Ing '''Balantakan''' (''Coix lacryma-jobi''), a king Ingles, ausan dang ''Job's Tears'', ''Coixseed'', ''adlay'', o ''adlai'', metung yang matas a tanaman kareng mangapaling lugal a mamungang binutil ibat king familiang [[Poaceae]] (familia da reng dikut) a tubu king [[Aslagan]]g [[Asia]] ampong peninsular  [[Malaysia]]. Kareng aliwang lugal, tatanam de kareng mula antimong tanaman a [[:en:Annual plant|annual]] o banuahan. Megi neng karaniwan a tanaman kareng mangapaling lugal king mauling dake ning [[:en:United States|Estados Unidos]] ampo king [[:en:New World|Bayung Yatu]] o ''New World''. Maralas, pisasali da la reng balantakan king makabaligong lagiung ''Chinese pearl barley'' kareng [[:en:Asian supermarket|Asian supermarket]] king America, lipat ning ing ''C. lacryma-jobi'' e ne kapareu genus ning ''[[:en:barley|barley]]'' o ''Hordeum vulgare''.

Two varieties of the species are grown. ''Coix lacryma-jobi'' var. ''lacryma-jobi'' has hard shelled pseudocarps which are very hard, pearly white, oval structures used as beads for making [[Rosary|rosaries]], necklaces, and other objects. ''Coix lacryma-jobi'' var. ''ma-yuen''<!--is this named for [[Ma Yuan (Han Dynasty)]]?--> is harvested as a [[cereal]] crop and is used medicinally in parts of Asia.
Adua lang ''variety'' ning species deng tatanam da. Ing ''Coix lacryma-jobi'' var. ''lacryma-jobi'' atin yang mangaragul a pseudocarp a masias ampong maputing anting perlas, at maki tabas a tulungkaba (''oval''), a magagamit kareng kuintas ampong rosario ampong aliwang bage. Ing ''Coix lacryma-jobi'' var. ''ma-yuen''<!--is this named for [[Ma Yuan (Han Dynasty)]]?--> pupupulan de antinmong binutil, ati gagamitan deng panulu kareng mapilang dake ning Asia. 

